An Akure Magistrates Court has ordered for the remand of a 19-year-old man, Babatunde Bobola at the Correctional Centre, in Akure, Ondo State, for allegedly raping an eight-year-old girl. The men of the Ondo State Security Network Agency also known as Amotekun Corps arrested the defendant for allegedly committing the crime in Akure on March 24, 2022. He was charged to court and arraigned on one-count of rape. At the proceeding, the state Prosecutor, O.F Akeredolu told the court that the defendant had carnal knowledge of victim. The charge read in part: “That you, Babatunde Bobola, on or about March 24, 2022, at about 16:00 hours, at Odige Street, Akure, a place within the criminal jurisdiction of this Honourable Court, did have carnal knowledge of, an eight-year-old girl.” According to the prosecutor, the offences contravene Sections 357 and 358 of the Criminal Code Law, Cap. 37, Vol. 1, Laws of Ondo State of Nigeria, 2006 Giving the nature of the offence against the defendant, Akeredolu prayed for an order to remand him at the correctional centre, which was supported by an affidavit. The defendant pleaded not guilty but his plea was not taken. The Magistrate, N.K. Aladejana remanded the defendant in the Olokuta Correctional Centre pending the insurance of legal advice from the Department of Public Prosecution . He adjourned the case till June 13, 2022, for further mention. Copyright PUNCH. All rights reserved. This material, and other digital content on this website, may not be reproduced, published, broadcast, rewritten or redistributed in whole or in part without prior express written permission from PUNCH. Contact: theeditor@punchng.com